01:14:48.540 --> 01:14:52.050
- In the mid 1980s, I
decided to take a four-month

01:14:52.050 --> 01:14:53.940
sabbatical from my law practice.

01:14:53.940 --> 01:14:55.290
- [Lex] Yes.

01:14:55.290 --> 01:14:57.120
- Professor James Vorenberg,

01:14:57.120 --> 01:14:59.940
who was at the time Dean
of the Harvard Law School,

01:14:59.940 --> 01:15:02.820
heard about it, heard
about it from his wife,

01:15:02.820 --> 01:15:06.780
Elizabeth Betty Vorenberg,
whom I was very friendly with,

01:15:06.780 --> 01:15:10.950
because we were both on the
ACLU of Massachusetts board,

01:15:10.950 --> 01:15:11.783
at the time.

01:15:12.720 --> 01:15:17.720
And so Betty told Jim that
Harvey was taking a sabbatical.

01:15:19.590 --> 01:15:23.550
Jim called Harvey and asked
Harvey if he would like to teach

01:15:23.550 --> 01:15:27.630
a course at the Harvard Law
School because there was nobody

01:15:27.630 --> 01:15:32.490
who had teaching criminal
law from the perspective

01:15:32.490 --> 01:15:35.940
of somebody who actually
was in court and litigated.

01:15:35.940 --> 01:15:37.233
It was all theoretical.

01:15:38.310 --> 01:15:39.687
I said, "Sure, I'll do it."

01:15:40.560 --> 01:15:43.353
So, I taught a semester
at Harvard Law School.

01:15:44.190 --> 01:15:46.890
The student evaluations
were fabulous. Why?

01:15:46.890 --> 01:15:48.270
Because it was really interesting.

01:15:48.270 --> 01:15:51.270
They were hearing a lawyer
who's talking about real cases.

01:15:51.270 --> 01:15:53.340
I actually brought in a few of my clients

01:15:53.340 --> 01:15:55.980
to some of the classes.

01:15:55.980 --> 01:15:58.627
And so Jim called me in and said,

01:15:58.627 --> 01:16:01.290
"Harvey, the students love this course.

01:16:01.290 --> 01:16:02.190
I'd like to offer you

01:16:02.190 --> 01:16:05.280
a tenure track position at the law school.

01:16:05.280 --> 01:16:06.780
You'd have to give up your law practice."

01:16:06.780 --> 01:16:08.580
I turned him down.

01:16:08.580 --> 01:16:11.280
He said, "Did you just say 'No'?"

01:16:11.280 --> 01:16:13.620
I said, "Yes, I said, 'No.'"

01:16:13.620 --> 01:16:14.580
He said, "How come?"

01:16:14.580 --> 01:16:18.480
He says, "Nobody in my administration

01:16:18.480 --> 01:16:20.850
has ever turned down a tenure track offer

01:16:20.850 --> 01:16:22.728
at Harvard Law School."

01:16:22.728 --> 01:16:27.150
I said, "Because I could
see that I'm not a good fit.

01:16:27.150 --> 01:16:32.150
That the administrators
are overrun the place.

01:16:32.430 --> 01:16:35.190
That faculty members,
especially untenured,

01:16:35.190 --> 01:16:37.290
are afraid to say things

01:16:37.290 --> 01:16:40.593
that might not help them
in the tenure quest.

01:16:43.226 --> 01:16:45.300
It's not a good fit for me."

01:16:45.300 --> 01:16:47.910
- [Lex] You saw this in
the mid 1980s, already?

01:16:47.910 --> 01:16:49.020
- Yes, about 1985.

01:16:50.520 --> 01:16:53.880
And I went back to my law practice.

01:16:53.880 --> 01:16:58.080
I did not want to get
into this meat grinder

01:16:58.080 --> 01:16:59.400
that I saw.

01:16:59.400 --> 01:17:02.520
Actually, I started to see it,

01:17:02.520 --> 01:17:04.110
before the turn of the century,

01:17:04.110 --> 01:17:07.233
because I co-authored "The
Shadow University" in '98,

01:17:08.100 --> 01:17:11.100
and then co-founded FIRE in '99.

01:17:11.100 --> 01:17:14.823
I'm an early student of this phenomenon.

01:17:15.750 --> 01:17:17.767
- What are some other
aspects of this, the book,

01:17:17.767 --> 01:17:21.540
"The Shadow University",
that we may have not covered?

01:17:21.540 --> 01:17:23.430
- Well, let me tell you a story.

01:17:23.430 --> 01:17:24.767
I believe I tell it in
"The Shadow University",

01:17:24.767 --> 01:17:26.670
'cause it was part of-

01:17:26.670 --> 01:17:28.470
- [Lex] I'm loving these stories, Harvey.

01:17:28.470 --> 01:17:30.660
- The stories are fabulous.

01:17:30.660 --> 01:17:32.210
Let me tell you a story of...

01:17:34.164 --> 01:17:37.683
I did a tour of the
country, visiting campuses.

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:41.757
I visited a college
called Hamline University.

01:17:41.757 --> 01:17:45.120
I believe it was in Indiana or Illinois.

01:17:45.120 --> 01:17:46.383
Somewhere in the Midwest.

01:17:47.250 --> 01:17:50.520
